dataExt.exDesc: The resource extent occupies the whole state of Nebraska.

dataIdInfo.idPurp: This dataset provides location information of properties across the state that are either owned, managed, or leased by the Nebraska Game and Parks Commission. The purpose of the data set is to assist the Nebraska Game and Parks Commission (NGPC) in management of its properties.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: The Nebraska Game and Parks Commission Property boundary data set is a digital representation of property under the control of the Nebraska Game and Parks Commission (NGPC) and the State of Nebraska. The properties represented in the data may be owned, managed, or leased by the Commision. The data set covers the state of Nebraska and includes areas such as Wildlife Management Areas (WMA), State Fish Hatcheries (FH), State Parks (SP), State Recreation Areas (SRA), and State Historical Parks (SHP). The Property Areas dataset includes all combined parcels for a particular area name, and groups the parcels together to give data users the overall picture of the boundary constraints.
dataIdInfo.idCredit: Acknowledgement of the Nebraska Game and Parks Commission would be appreciated in products derived from this data.

Consts.useLimit: These data are digitized by NGPC staff. Boundaries may not match perfectly with those produced by county assessors, nor were they necessarily drawn based on survey-grade maps. The data do not comply with FGDC Cadastral Standards. Acknowledgement of the Nebraska Game and Parks Commission would be appreciated in products derived from these data.The data remain the property of the Nebraska Game and Parks Commission.The data are provided for research, educational, and outreach purposes only.This data set is not designed for use as a regulatory tool in permitting or citing decisions.This is public information and may be interpreted by organizations, agencies, units of government, or others based on needs; however, they are responsible for the appropriate application. Federal, State, or local regulatory bodies are not to reassign to the NGPC any authority for the decisions that they make. The NGPC will not perform any evaluations of these maps for purposes related solely to State or local regulatory programs.Digital data files are periodically updated. Data users are responsible for obtaining the latest version of the data.
